  "description": "A comprehensive neuroimaging dataset investigating decision-making under risk and ambiguity, comprising structural and functional MRI, diffusion-weighted imaging, and concurrent EEG recordings during transcranial magnetic stimulation of parietal regions in 53 healthy young adults. The dataset enables investigation of parietal cortex involvement and its interactions with other brain regions during probabilistic decision-making with uncertain outcomes.",
  "methods_description": "Data collection included structural MRI (T1-weighted, T2-weighted, and diffusion-weighted imaging), functional MRI during task performance, and concurrent EEG recordings during inhibitory transcranial magnetic stimulation applied over two parietal regions and the vertex in 53 healthy volunteers aged 18-31 years.",
